68, five under par, after the first round of the Australian Masters
yesterday in Melbourne.
Garbutt, a former English amateur champion, is competing in Australia
after losing his European Tour card, while Teravainen has enjoyed only
moderate success on the Australian Tour in recent years.
Tom Watson, Robert Allenby and Peter Senior finished one shot adrift
of the leaders, while former US PGA champion John Daly took 71.
Watson said he was heartened by his form on the greens. ''That's the
best round I've putted this year,'' said the former British and US Open
champion.
