<DATE>950217</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Weather data</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>22</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979812498</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
FARMERS, market gardeners and contractors can now get weather data on
computer screen as the information has been prepared by the Met Office.
This 24 hours a day system is Metereological Information Self-briefing
Terminal (MIST) provides up-to-the-minute information for planning
weather senstitive operations
Data will include rainfall radar, temperature forecasts, local area
forecasts and surface Atlantic charts.
To run the system the user must have a 486DX computer plus modem and
the annual licence fee for MIST is #299 plus VAT
</TEXT>
