<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH950217-000036</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950217-000036</DOCID>
<DATE>950217</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Norcros warns of earnings loss</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>21</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979812504</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
NORCROS, the building materials and print and packaging group,
yesterday warned shareholders it expected to report a pre-tax loss for
the year to March 31 after provisions for reorganisation and property
writedowns.
''As a result, the level of the final dividend, if any, will not be
maintained at its previous level,'' added the company, which is based at
Bracknell, Berkshire.
In the previous 12 months it made profits before tax of #17.1m and
paid a final dividend of 3.5p per share.
The reorganisation costs will relate to the building materials
division, where the group said a fundamental review was now taking place
with the aim of restoring its long-term competitiveness.
A provision will also be made in the discontinuing property division
to reduce the book value of its properties to current market value
following recent changes in planning approval relating to the largest
development at Braintree, Essex.
Norcros said the board was also undertaking a major review of the
group's businesses and was in discussions with a number of parties
regarding the potential disposal of some subsidiary companies.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
