<DOCNO>GH950217-000037</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950217-000037</DOCID>
<DATE>950217</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Albright at 150p</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>21</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979812505</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE current hostile City attitude towards new issues has forced down
the flotation price of chemicals group Albright &amp; Wilson to just 150p
which values the phosphoric acid company at just #470m.
That compares with the #600m expected at the beginning of the year
when a share price of near 200p had been bandied around.
Profits for 1994 amounted to #60.9m or #40.7m after exceptional
rationalisation costs.
At 150p, the shares are being offered at about 10 times current year
earnings which is a 35% discount to the chemicals sector.
Lists close next Friday and dealings begin on March 8.
</TEXT>
