<HEADLINE>Murder plea</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>11</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979812533</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
DETECTIVES investigating the murder of convicted child molester
Lawrence Leydon, of Southhouse Medway, Edinburgh, yesterday asked people
who knew him to contact them. Mr Leydon is known to have been at a local
shop at 7pm on Saturday, the evening he was murdered. Detective
Superintendent Alec Brown, who is leading the investigation, said: ''In
spite of much speculation about Mr Leydon's background, there is still
little factual evidence to suggest this was purely a revenge attack.''
