<HEADLINE>Runway repairs</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>10</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979812539</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
INCOMING flights to Shetland were delayed yesterday after a three-foot
hole was discovered in the runway, apparently caused by recent heavy
rain. Airport staff noticed the tarmac was cracking on Wednesday
afternoon and contractors worked overnight, repairing the damage by late
yesterday morning. Departing aircraft were able to take off, but
northbound flights were delayed for several hours.
</TEXT>
