<HEADLINE>Double helping</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>10</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979812540</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE second Perth Food Festival, a celebration of the area's culinary
delicacies, will be bigger and better it was announced yesterday. A
lavish feast will be served up between Friday April 28 and Saturday May
6 -- twice the length of last year's event -- at various locations
throughout the city. Local schoolchildren will be involved through
competitions and there will be a series of themed dinners at hotels and
restaurants.
