<HEADLINE>Flares response</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>10</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979812541</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
AN international rescue operation was launched yesterday near Gruinard
Island in Wester Ross, after four flares were spotted by a military
aircraft involved with British and Dutch warships on exercise. An RAF
Nimrod joined coastguards in the hunt -- which failed to find anything
-- while a coastguard helicopter checked local mountain ranges for a
possible climber in distress.
