<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH950217-000077</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950217-000077</DOCID>
<DATE>950217</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Union backs EU disaster inquiry</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>10</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979812545</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE Transport and General Workers Union in Scotland is backing a
petition calling on the European Parliament to ask the European
Commission to investigate the Lockerbie bombing in December 1988, in
which 270 died.
The petition was launched by British victims' relatives, who were not
satisfied by a fatal accident inquiry in Dumfries because of its
limitations.
</TEXT>
