<HEADLINE>Open university</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>10</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979812564</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SOUTH African golfer Gary Player is to receive an honorary Doctor of
Laws degree at St Andrews University in July. The winner of more than
150 international titles will be presented at the ''home of golf'' where
he will be playing in his 41st consecutive Open championship. He first
won the Open at Muirfield in 1959, with later victories at Carnoustie in
1968, and Royal Lytham and St Anne's in 1974. Jack Nicklaus was
presented with an honorary degree by St Andrews University in 1984.
</TEXT>
