<HEADLINE>Brown inquiry</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979812585</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
WASHINGTON: The US Justice Department has opened a preliminary
criminal investigation of Commerce Seretary Ron Brown's personal
financial dealings. The decision announced by Attorney General Janet
Reno means that the department has found specific and credible
allegations that Brown may have committed a federal felony. The
department has 90 days to decide if there is enough evidence to ask a
special court to name an independent prosecutor for a full criminal
investigation.
</TEXT>
