<DOCID>GH950217-000170</DOCID>
<DATE>950217</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Three prisoners escape from van</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979812638</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THREE prisoners were on the run last night after escaping from a
police van on the M80 on their way from court in Falkirk to Glasgow's
Barlinnie Prison.
Chief Inspector Mike Morrow, at Stenhousemuir, said the three men made
their escape at about 5pm near Bankhead interchange, Denny.
He said the three apparently burst open the rear door of the police
van in slow-moving rush-hour traffic after one prisoner slipped his
handcuffs.
Five other prisoners in the van made no moves to escape, and were
taken on to Barlinnie.
Mr Morrow said search teams were looking for the three, two of whom
might still be handcuffed together.
One man is described as 6ft 1in tall, with a skinhead haircut, light
brown hair, and wearing a maroon top under a black overtop, jeans and
black boots.
The second is 5ft 10in, with short dark hair and was wearing a blue
check shirt, black jumper and jeans.
The third is around 6ft, slim, with short black hair in a crewcut with
long sideboards. He was wearing a denim shirt, dark bomber jacket and
white trousers.
</TEXT>
